trend_summary: Across the time-stamped scenes the tightly gridded downtown fabric remains intact, yet vacant corners and surface parking lots steadily disappear, replaced by larger roofplates and a few taller blocks. Tree cover thickens along streets and parks, while several construction sites migrate block to block, signalling continuous infill and modernization rather than outward sprawl.
notable_changes: Conversion of several brownfield or parking parcels into new mid-rise buildings.
Noticeable increase in street-tree and courtyard vegetation, especially around central circle.
Replacement of smaller roof structures with larger, lighter rooftops indicating new office complexes.
Periodic construction cranes and cleared lots shift location between images, showing rolling redevelopment.
Slight widening or greening of diagonal avenue medians, enhancing public realm.
